$lang['How do you convert a Decimal to a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Aw yu kin kɔnvɔyt Dɛsimal to Ɛksadesimal?';
$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Fɔ kɔnvɔyt dɛsimal to heksadesimal na simpul tin, ɛn yu kin du am wit kɔlkyulɛta ɔ ɔnlayn kɔnvɔta. Fɔ mek yu ebul fɔ chenj di nɔmba, sheb am wit 16 ɛn tek di ɔda wan. Dis lef go afta dat kɔrɛspɔnd to wan heksadesimal dijit. Fɔ ɛgzampul, if yu gɛt di dɛsimal nɔmba 234, sheb am wit 16 ɛn tek di ɔda wan: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. So, insay heksadesimal noteshɔn, dɛn go rayt dis nɔmba as “E2”.';
