$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Hɛksadesimal na we fɔ riprizent baynary data insay fɔm we mɔtalman kin rid. Dɛn bin mek am insay di ia 1900 fɔ mek kɔmpyuta dɛn ebul fɔ kip bɔku bɔku tin dɛn.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Yu kin yuz heksadesimal fɔ kɔnvɔyt bitwin dɛsimal ɛn baynary valyu dɛn. Fɔ ɛgzampul, if yu kɔnvɔyt 10011011001010 to heksadesimal, dat go mek yu gɛt 0x4F. Dis min se di valyu 4F de sho di baynary nɔmba 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Insay matematiks ɛn kɔmpyuta sayɛns, heksadesimal (we dɛn kin yuz bak bays 16, ɔ heks) na pozishɔnal nɔmba sistɛm we gɛt radiks, ɔ bays, we na 16. I de yuz siksti difrɛn simbul dɛn, bɔku tɛm di simbul dɛn 0–9 fɔ riprizent valyu dɛn ziro to nayn, . ɛn A, B, C, D, E, F (ɔ ɔda we a–f) fɔ riprizent valyu dɛn tɛn to fayvtin. Fɔ ɛgzampul, di heksadesimal nɔmba 2AF3 ikwal, insay dɛsimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , ɔ 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Ɛni heksadesimal dijit de sho 4 baynary dijit (bit) (dɛn kin kɔl am bak &quot;nibble&quot;), ɛn di praymar yus fɔ heksadesimal noteshɔn na as mɔtalman-frenli ripreshɔn fɔ baynary kɔd valyu dɛn na kɔmpiutishɔn ɛn dijital ilɛktroniks. Fɔ ɛgzampul, bayt valyu dɛn kin kɔmɔt frɔm 0 to 255 (dɛsimal) bɔt dɛn kin ripresent dɛn mɔ izi wan as tu heksadesimal dijit dɛn we de na di rɛnj 00 to FF. Dɛn kin yuz heksadesimal bak fɔ sho kɔmpyuta mɛmori adrɛs dɛn.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Heks na abbrevieshɔn fɔ Hexadecimal, we de bays pan wan bays -16 strɔkchɔ ɛn dɛn de yuz am fɔ mek i izi fɔ mek i izi fɔ mek dɛn ripresent instrɔkshɔn to kɔmpyuta dɛn. Dɛn bin mek dis 16 simbul nɔmba sistɛm as we fɔ mek dɛn nɔ gɛt 8-bit baynary nɔmba, so dɛn kin kɔd di data insay kɔmpyuta dɛn we nɔ gɛt ɛni tray. Yu kin imprint ɛn tayp am yuz tu difrɛn heks dijit dɛn wit ɛni heks dijit we de sho wan nibbul ɔ sɔntɛm 4-bit fɔmat.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Dis nɔmba sistɛm de yuz 16 simbul dɛn we dɛn riprizent insay wan rɛnj frɔm 0-9 ɔ AF. Di 0–9 riprizent nɔmba dɛn we go rich nayn usay AF de riprizent bay di nɔmba 10–15. As yu kɔmpia am wit di ɔda tri kayn nɔmba sistɛm dɛn, dɛn kin tek di heksadesimal nɔmba sistɛm as di wan we wok pas ɔl.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Yu heksadesimal kɔd nɔ valid';
